.TH "mipi_dsi_dcs_write" 9 "mipi_dsi_dcs_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mipi_dsi_dcs_write \- send DCS write command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" mipi_dsi_dcs_write
.BI "(struct mipi_dsi_device *dsi "  ","
.BI "u8 cmd "  ","
.BI "const void *data "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dsi" 12
DSI peripheral device
.IP "cmd" 12
DCS command
.IP "data" 12
buffer containing the command payload
.IP "len" 12
command payload length
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will automatically choose the right data type depending on
the command payload length.
.SH "RETURN"
The number of bytes successfully transmitted or a negative error
code on failure.
